      ],
      "parameters": {
        "width": 400,
        "height": 928,
        "content": "\n## ‚öôÔ∏è Setup Instructions\n\n### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Connect Slack API\n1. Create an app ‚Üí <https://api.slack.com/apps>  \n2. **OAuth & Permissions** ‚Üí add scopes you need to read channel history (typical:  \n   `channels:history`, `groups:history`, `im:history`, `mpim:history`, plus `channels:read`, `groups:read`, `users:read`. Add `chat:write` if you want the bot to reply in Slack.)  \n3. **Install** the app to your workspace ‚Üí copy the **Bot User OAuth Token**  \n4. In n8n ‚Üí **Credentials ‚Üí New ‚Üí Slack OAuth2 API** ‚Üí paste token and save  \n5. In the **Slack History** node, select your Slack credential and the **Channel ID** to read\n\n\n\n\n## üì¨ Contact\nNeed help customizing this (e.g., filtering by list, or sending reports by email/Slack)?  \n\nüìß **robert@ynteractive.com**  \nüîó **[Robert Breen](https://www.linkedin.com/in/robert-breen-29429625/)**  \nüåê **[ynteractive.com](https://ynteractive.com)**\n"
      },
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
